## The same sunrise. Just yours.

There is a moment, a few minutes before dawn over Luxor, when a dozen balloons hang in the dark waiting for the light — and every one of them is a big basket packed with twenty people angling for the rail. The view is extraordinary no matter what. But the experience is a shared one: shoulders, elbows, someone else's selfie stick in the frame of the best photograph of your whole trip.

A private VIP flight quietly removes all of that. Same route, same sunrise, same three thousand years coming up gold beneath you — but the basket is yours, the pilot is flying for you alone, and the morning belongs to your group and nobody else.

## What the exclusivity actually buys you

It's not about luxury for its own sake. A private basket changes the *feeling* of the flight: it's calmer, quieter, and more personal. You can move to whichever side the light is best on. The pilot talks to you, not a crowd. And when you drift up over the Valley of the Kings, the Ramesseum and Hatshepsut's terraces with the Nile a ribbon of green below, there's no one between you and it.

This is the flight people choose for the mornings that matter — a honeymoon, a proposal, a landmark birthday, or simply the once-in-a-lifetime sunrise they refuse to share.

> The shared balloon gives you the view. The private one gives you the moment.

## Arranged so all you do is watch the sun come up

We handle everything: the pre-dawn pickup from your hotel, the licensed operator and pilot, the permits and the ground crew, and your consigliere on call the whole time. Ballooning is weather-dependent everywhere on earth — so if conditions call your flight off, we re-fly you free another morning where we can, or refund it in full.

You bring a warm layer for the early chill, a camera, and the willingness to be somewhere genuinely unforgettable before breakfast. Prefer to fly as part of the shared sunrise balloon instead? That's superb value, and we arrange that too — just ask.
